<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="I" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Induce" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Induce,</orth> to move, to prevail on, to determine: <bibl n="shak. mm 4.3.53" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. IV, 3, 53</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h8 2.4.76" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 II, 4, 76</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cor 1.9.16" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. I, 9, 16</bibl>. With <cit><quote>to:</quote> <bibl n="shak. tn 5.315" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. V, 315</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. h8 2.4.151" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 II, 4, 151</bibl>. With an inf.: <bibl n="shak. tit 5.3.79" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. V, 3, 79</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 2.4.63" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. II, 4, 63</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 2.4.63" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. II, 4, 63</bibl> Used of things, == to obtain: <cit><quote>to i. their mediation,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ant 5.2.169" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. V, 2, 169</bibl></cit>.
